---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Home"
  description="Official information about the UK Armed Forces Compensation Scheme (AFCS). Learn about eligibility, compensation, and support services for service personnel and veterans.">
  <div class="container my-5">
    <h1 class="display-4 mb-4">Armed Forces Compensation Scheme</h1>
    <div class="row g-4">
      <div class="col-md-8">
        <p class="lead">The Armed Forces Compensation Scheme (AFCS) provides compensation for any injury, illness, or death caused by service in the UK Armed Forces on or after 6 April 2005.</p>
        <div class="card mb-4">
          <div class="card-body">
            <h2 class="h4">Quick Links</h2>
            <div class="row">
              <div class="col-md-6">
                <ul class="list-unstyled">
                  <li><a href="/eligibility" class="text-decoration-none">Check Eligibility</a></li>
                  <li><a href="/compensation" class="text-decoration-none">Types of Compensation</a></li>
                  <li><a href="/support" class="text-decoration-none">Support Services</a></li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div class="col-md-6">
                <ul class="list-unstyled">
                  <li><a href="/policy" class="text-decoration-none">Policy Information</a></li>
                  <li><a href="/financial" class="text-decoration-none">Financial Advice</a></li>
                  <li><a href="/medical" class="text-decoration-none">Medical Care</a></li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <h2 class="h3 mb-3">About the Armed Forces Compensation Scheme</h2>
        <p>The Armed Forces Compensation Scheme (AFCS) is a comprehensive programme designed to support UK service personnel and veterans who have suffered injuries, illnesses, or disabilities as a result of their service. Established in 2005, the scheme aims to provide fair and just compensation to those who have made sacrifices in the line of duty.</p>
        <p>Our team of experts specialises in guiding service members and veterans through the complex process of applying for AFCS benefits. We understand the unique challenges faced by those who have served our country, and we are committed to ensuring that every eligible individual receives the full support and compensation they deserve.</p>
        <h3 class="h4 mb-3">Key Features of the AFCS</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Compensation for injuries and illnesses caused or made worse by service</li>
          <li>Coverage for both physical and mental health conditions</li>
          <li>Lump sum payments for pain and suffering</li>
          <li>Guaranteed Income Payments for more severe disabilities</li>
          <li>Support for bereaved families</li>
          <li>Access to rehabilitation and vocational support services</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Whether you're a currently serving member of the Armed Forces or a veteran, understanding your rights and the benefits available to you is crucial. Our website provides comprehensive information on eligibility criteria, types of compensation, application processes, and additional support services to help you navigate the AFCS effectively.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-4">
        <div class="card bg-light mb-4">
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3 class="h5">Need Assistance?</h3>
            <p>Contact our helpline for guidance:</p>
            <p class="fw-bold">0800 XXX XXXX</p>
            <p class="small">Monday to Friday, 8am to 6pm</p>
            <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Get Support</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3 class="h5">Latest Updates</h3>
            <ul class="list-unstyled">
              <li class="mb-2"><a href="#" class="text-decoration-none">New AFCS policy changes for 2023</a></li>
              <li class="mb-2"><a href="#" class="text-decoration-none">Expanded mental health support services</a></li>
              <li><a href="#" class="text-decoration-none">Upcoming AFCS information webinars</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
